      "writtenOn": "2015-07-13T20:53:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: try to keep headers in alphabetical order whenever possible. Looks like this wasn\u0027t done in a previous patch, but that would get you:\n\n  android/skin/event.h\n  android/skin/qt/battery-window.h\n  android/skin/qt/sms-window.h\n  android/skin/qt/tool-window.h\n  android/skin/surface.h\n  android/skin/winsys.h\n\nThis is done to reduce merge conflicts when two people are modifying the same source file. It also avoids having to think about the best location.\n\nAlso, normally, the best header inclusion order is:\n\n  1) [for source files only] corresponding header\n  2) headers from the same directory or logical component\n  3) third-party library headers (e.g. Qt ones here).\n  3) system headers.\n\nThe idea is to avoid having one of your headers breaking if a specific third-party or system header isn\u0027t included first.",
      "revId": "d6b3b33937c6f202197186b9195d6884c70bd5a2",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
